{"comments":"Optical dispersion — wavelength-dependent refraction.\n\n## What is Dispersion?\n\nDispersion occurs because a material's refractive index varies with light\nwavelength. Blue light bends more than red light. This creates:\n- Rainbows (sunlight through water droplets)\n- \"Fire\" in gemstones (spectral colors flashing)\n- Chromatic aberration in lenses\n\n## Abbe Number (Vd)\n\nThe Abbe number quantifies dispersion. Higher Abbe = lower dispersion:\n\nVd = (nd - 1) / (nF - nC)\n\nWhere:\n- nd = refractive index at 587.6 nm (helium d-line, yellow)\n- nF = refractive index at 486.1 nm (hydrogen F-line, blue)\n- nC = refractive index at 656.3 nm (hydrogen C-line, red)\n\n## Value Ranges\n\n- **High dispersion** (20-30): Dense flint glass, gemstones with \"fire\"\n- **Medium dispersion** (30-50): Crown glass, common materials\n- **Low dispersion** (50-95): Fluorite, special optical glasses\n\n## Gemstone \"Fire\"\n\nDispersion creates the \"fire\" (spectral flashes) in gemstones:\n- Diamond: 0.044 (exceptional fire)\n- Moissanite: 0.104 (more fire than diamond!)\n- Cubic zirconia: 0.060 (good fire)\n- Ruby/sapphire: 0.018 (subtle fire)\n\nFire value = (nB - nR) where nB is blue IOR and nR is red IOR.\n\n## Why This Matters\n\nAt billion-agent scale, dispersion determines:\n- Gemstone appearance (fire, brilliance, scintillation)\n- Lens design (achromatic doublets need high/low Abbe pairs)\n- Rainbow rendering (atmospheric effects)\n- Prism effects (spectral separation)\n\n## Data Sources\n\nSchott optical glass catalog, GIA gemological data, CRC Handbook.\n","declarations":[{"children":[{"comments":null,"info":{"declType":"instance","dependencies":[],"type":{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Data","Eq"],"Eq"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Hydrogen","Schema","Physical","Optical","Dispersion"],"AbbeNumber"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"}},"sourceSpan":{"end":[168,46],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Physical/Optical/Dispersion.purs","start":[168,1]},"title":"eqAbbeNumber"},{"comments":null,"info":{"declType":"instance","dependencies":[],"type":{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Data","Ord"],"Ord"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Hydrogen","Schema","Physical","Optical","Dispersion"],"AbbeNumber"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"}},"sourceSpan":{"end":[169,48],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Physical/Optical/Dispersion.purs","start":[169,1]},"title":"ordAbbeNumber"},{"comments":null,"info":{"declType":"instance","dependencies":[],"type":{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Data","Show"],"Show"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Hydrogen","Schema","Physical","Optical","Dispersion"],"AbbeNumber"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"}},"sourceSpan":{"end":[172,49],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Physical/Optical/Dispersion.purs","start":[171,1]},"title":"showAbbeNumber"}],"comments":"Abbe number (Vd) — reciprocal dispersion [15.0, 100.0].\n\n## Bounds Rationale\n\n- Lower bound 15.0: Below most dense flint glasses (~17)\n- Upper bound 100.0: Above calcium fluoride (~95)\n\nHigher Abbe number = lower dispersion (less rainbow effect).\n","info":{"dataDeclType":"newtype","declType":"data","roles":[],"typeArguments":[]},"kind":null,"sourceSpan":{"end":[166,39],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Physical/Optical/Dispersion.purs","start":[166,1]},"title":"AbbeNumber"},{"children":[],"comments":"Create AbbeNumber with validation.\n","info":{"declType":"value","type":{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Function"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Number"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Data","Maybe"],"Maybe"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Hydrogen","Schema","Physical","Optical","Dispersion"],"AbbeNumber"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"}],"tag":"TypeApp"}},"kind":null,"sourceSpan":{"end":[175,41],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Physical/Optical/Dispersion.purs","start":[175,1]},"title":"abbeNumber"},{"children":[],"comments":"Create AbbeNumber with clamping.\n","info":{"declType":"value","type":{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Function"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Number"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Hydrogen","Schema","Physical","Optical","Dispersion"],"AbbeNumber"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"}},"kind":null,"sourceSpan":{"end":[181,41],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Physical/Optical/Dispersion.purs","start":[181,1]},"title":"abbeNumberUnsafe"},{"children":[],"comments":"Extract the underlying Number.\n","info":{"declType":"value","type":{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Function"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Hydrogen","Schema","Physical","Optical","Dispersion"],"AbbeNumber"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Number"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"}},"kind":null,"sourceSpan":{"end":[185,35],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Physical/Optical/Dispersion.purs","start":[185,1]},"title":"unwrapAbbe"},{"children":[],"comments":"Bounds documentation for Abbe number.\n","info":{"declType":"value","type":{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Hydrogen","Schema","Bounded"],"NumberBounds"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}},"kind":null,"sourceSpan":{"end":[189,35],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Physical/Optical/Dispersion.purs","start":[189,1]},"title":"abbeBounds"},{"children":[{"comments":null,"info":{"declType":"instance","dependencies":[],"type":{"annotation":[],"conte